node.title: NSW fast tracks freedoms for fully vaccinated people, but bad news for those without COVID-19 jab
node.alt: a group of young women and men stand in front a dj dancing
node.description: The NSW government has made significant changes to the state's COVID-19 roadmap, bringing forward new freedoms for fully vaccinated people and delaying privileges for those who've shunned the jab.
node.content:
["The NSW government has made significant changes to the state's COVID-19 roadmap, bringing forward new freedoms for fully vaccinated people and delaying privileges for those who've shunned the jab.", "A raft of restrictions due to be scrapped for people fully inoculated on December 1 will now be relaxed on Monday, November 8.", "Unvaccinated people had also been due to get freedoms on December 1.", "However, they'll now have to wait until December 15, or, whatever date NSW reaches 95 per cent double dose coverage for people aged 16 and above.", "In NSW, 93.6 per cent of people aged 16 and up have had one jab, while 87.8 per cent are fully vaccinated.", "The changes are due to be announced later today.", "The original freedoms for December 1 included lifting restrictions on the number of visitors to the home, informal outdoor gatherings and no\u00a0limits to hospitality settings.", "On Tuesday, the state recorded 173 new locally-acquired COVID-19 cases and another four deaths in the 24 hours to 8pm last night.", "There are now 333 people in hospital, 72 of whom require ventilation.", "More to come.", "", "
